---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = 'Terms & Conditions';
const description = 'Terms and conditions for working with Deck Masters.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24 bg-surface">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-neutral-900 tracking-tight uppercase">
        Terms &amp; Conditions
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-neutral-500">Last updated: March 9, 2026</p>

      <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-neutral-700">
        <p>
          These Terms &amp; Conditions (&quot;Terms&quot;) govern your use of Deck Masters&apos; website, communications,
          and services. By requesting an estimate, entering into a project, or otherwise engaging with us, you agree to
          these Terms.
        </p>

        <h2 class="mt-6 font-semibold text-neutral-900 text-base">1. Estimates &amp; Scope of Work</h2>
        <p>
          All estimates are provided based on the information available at the time of quoting. Final pricing and scope
          may be adjusted if site conditions, material availability, or requested changes differ from what was originally
          discussed. Any changes will be communicated and approved in writing.
        </p>

        <h2 class="mt-6 font-semibold text-neutral-900 text-base">2. Scheduling &amp; Access</h2>
        <p>
          Project start dates are estimates and may shift due to weather, permitting, supplier delays, or other factors
          beyond our control. You agree to provide reasonable access to the property, including power and clear working
          areas, for the duration of the project.
        </p>

        <h2 class="mt-6 font-semibold text-neutral-900 text-base">3. Payments</h2>
        <p>
          Payment schedules, deposits, and accepted payment methods will be outlined in your project agreement. Late
          payments may be subject to fees as described in your contract. Ownership of materials may remain with Deck
          Masters until payment is received in full.
        </p>

        <h2 class="mt-6 font-semibold text-neutral-900 text-base">4. Communications &amp; Messaging</h2>
        <p>
          By providing your contact information and agreeing to our Terms, you consent to receive phone calls, emails,
          and SMS messages related to scheduling, project updates, and service coordination. Messaging and data rates may
          apply. You can reply STOP to any SMS to opt out of non-essential text communications.
        </p>

        <h2 class="mt-6 font-semibold text-neutral-900 text-base">5. Marketing Communications</h2>
        <p>
          Separate from project-related communications, you may choose to opt in to receive promotional or marketing
          messages about new services, offers, or updates. Consent for marketing messages is not required to obtain a
          quote or complete a purchase. You can opt out of marketing communications at any time by following the
          unsubscribe instructions in the message.
        </p>

        <h2 class="mt-6 font-semibold text-neutral-900 text-base">6. Warranties &amp; Workmanship</h2>
        <p>
          Any workmanship or material warranties will be described in your agreement or on your invoice. Normal wear and
          tear, misuse, lack of maintenance, or modifications by others are not covered.
        </p>

        <h2 class="mt-6 font-semibold text-neutral-900 text-base">7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, Deck Masters is not liable for any indirect, incidental, or
          consequential damages arising from the use of our website, communications, or services. Our total liability in
          connection with any project is limited to the amounts actually paid for that project.
        </p>

        <h2 class="mt-6 font-semibold text-neutral-900 text-base">8. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms from time to time. When we do, we will revise the &quot;Last updated&quot; date
          above. Continued use of our website or services after changes become effective constitutes your acceptance of
          the updated Terms.
        </p>

        <h2 class="mt-6 font-semibold text-neutral-900 text-base">9. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about these Terms or your project, please contact us using the information on our
          Contact page.
        </p>

        <p class="mt-6 text-xs text-neutral-500">
          This page is provided for general informational purposes and does not replace the specific terms of your
          signed agreement or invoice, which will control in the event of any conflict.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

